    "created_at": "2014-08-01T13:01:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-01T13:01:57Z",
    "body": "The purpose of this was, I assume, to permit convenient linking to the specific method. A common pattern for permitting this but keeping it out of the way is having a link on the right (or the left for RTL languages), either at the far end or immediately after the text, hidden by default but shown on hover over the heading. The pilcrow (\u00b6) is a common choice for the marker to use for this. https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/settings/ is a simple example of this in practice.\n\nSuch a thing would free the actual method text for something else if desired.\n",
